@warhawk059377 | The Hawk I disagree. In fact, Xiaomi products are known for offering somewhat premium and durable products, at an affordable price point. 
Look at how OnePlus made a name for themselves. Their phone on launch was the OnePlus One, offering (at the time) TOP NOTCH, PREMIUM SPECS AND A DURABLE BUILD for prices of the Pocophone F1, if not cheaper. Till this day, people are rocking the original OnePlus One with no problem at all (apart from software because no more updates, and everything else is outdated). And now look at OnePlus. They've made a reputation for themselves that they can produce high quality, durable, premium smartphones for an affordable price. So much so that they can even increase the price of the phones they create each year and still have MORE people purchase them without hesitation. 
So my point is, you can produce a quality smartphone with top of the line specs, amazing hardware and premium features yet not have to worry about it faulting you in the long run, all for an affordable price.ï»¿
